<% task = quest_two_current_task %>
<% current_step = quest_two_current_step %>
<% total_steps = quest_two_tasks.size %>

<section class="space-y-6">
  <%- if current_step == 1 %>
  <p>
    The archive structure is back, and now it is time to load the data and learn how to read it. Your task is to seed the database
    with test data and verify that the system can build reports for agents, missions, and skills.
  </p>

  <p>
    First, run this command:
  </p>

  <div class="rounded-xl border border-amber-700/60 bg-amber-950/20 p-4">
    <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-amber-400 mb-3">Terminal command</div>
    <pre class="overflow-x-auto whitespace-pre-wrap text-sm text-amber-100">bundle exec rake db:seed</pre>
  </div>

  <p>
    Once it finishes, start working through the tasks. In each task you need to write an <code class="bg-gray-800 text-gray-300 px-2 py-1 rounded">ActiveRecord</code>
    query and make sure its result matches the expected output.
    Write your queries in <code class="bg-gray-800 text-gray-300 px-2 py-1 rounded">app/services/quest2_student_service.rb</code>; the method stubs for every task are already there.
    Pay attention to the test command shown in each task — it tells you which method will be called for verification.
    You can run that command in the terminal to inspect your result and compare it with the expected one.
    Or simply refresh the page — the result is loaded here too.
    Once the output matches, the next task will be unlocked.
    And yes: the service must return a string.
  </p>
  <% end %>

  <div class="rounded-xl border border-cyan-900/70 bg-cyan-950/20 p-4">
    <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-between gap-3">
      <div>
        <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-cyan-500 mb-2">Step <%= current_step %> of <%= total_steps %></div>
        <div class="text-lg font-semibold text-white"><%= task[:title][:en] %></div>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-full px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold <%= task[:solved] ? 'bg-green-500/20 text-green-300 border border-green-500/40' : 'bg-gray-800 text-gray-300 border border-gray-700' %>">
        <%= task[:solved] ? 'MATCHED' : 'WAITING' %>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-300"><%= task[:description][:en] %></p>
  </div>

  <div class="rounded-xl border border-amber-700/60 bg-amber-950/20 p-4">
    <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-amber-400 mb-3">Terminal command</div>
    <pre class="overflow-x-auto whitespace-pre-wrap text-sm text-amber-100"><%= task[:command] %></pre>
  </div>

  <div class="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-2">
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-green-700/60 bg-green-950/20 p-4">
      <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-green-400 mb-3">Expected output</div>
      <pre class="min-h-48 whitespace-pre-wrap text-sm leading-relaxed text-green-100"><%= task[:expected_output] %></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-xl border border-cyan-700/60 bg-cyan-950/20 p-4">
      <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-cyan-400 mb-3">Service output</div>
      <pre class="min-h-48 whitespace-pre-wrap text-sm leading-relaxed text-cyan-100"><%= task[:actual_output] %></pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-between gap-3 border-t border-gray-800 pt-4">
    <div class="flex gap-3">
      <% if current_step > 1 %>
        <%= link_to '← Previous step', quest_two_step_path(current_step - 1), class: 'px-4 py-2 rounded bg-gray-800 hover:bg-gray-700 text-sm text-white transition' %>
      <% end %>
    </div>

    <% if current_step < total_steps %>
      <% if task[:solved] %>
        <%= link_to 'Next →', quest_two_step_path(current_step + 1), class: 'px-4 py-2 rounded bg-cyan-700 hover:bg-cyan-600 text-sm font-semibold text-white transition' %>
      <% else %>
        <span class="px-4 py-2 rounded bg-gray-800 text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 cursor-not-allowed border border-gray-700">Next →</span>
      <% end %>
    <% else %>
      <span class="px-4 py-2 rounded bg-green-500/20 text-sm font-semibold text-green-300 border border-green-500/40">
        You can run <code class="bg-gray-800 text-gray-300 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">rails quest:accept[2]</code> and unlock the third quest.
        Except... we have not published it yet.
      </span>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</section>
